chart_description: This chart shows the start time of the AWS cluster autoscaler process in seconds since the Unix epoch. The AWS Cluster Autoscaler is a tool that automatically adjusts the size of an Auto Scaling group to add or remove EC2 instances based on the group's configured scaling policies.

dimension_descriptions.process_start_time_seconds: The time at which the AWS cluster autoscaler process started, measured in seconds since the Unix epoch.
